features: MARINE TINNED COPPER WIRE (OFC) - Our GearIT Marine Speaker Wire made of tinned copper is designed to withstand harsh outdoor conditions, specifically for ocean or beach side properties and deep sea ocean adventures. We use thick gauge tinned copper wire to protect from salt and rusting due to high salt content on deep sea trips.

OCEAN SALT WATERPROOF - Our thick pvc jacket is waterproof and able to be used for salt water protection. Use for marine speakers, loudspeakers, or marine tower speakers for long lasting and durable waterproof speaker wire jackets.

THICK MARINE GAUGE WIRE - Tinned Wire 99.9% Oxygen Free Copper 2 Conductors (2C) with Red-Black internal cable color for easy polarity identification. External pvc jacket color is white cable lining. Insulation resists salt water, battery acid, oil, gasoline, heat, abrasion, and UV resistant radiation.

MARINE GRADE INSULATED CABLE - Perfect for radio, automotive, auto trailer, stereo, lighting, r/c under harsh outdoor conditions. UL Listed and CL3 Rated certification for marine wire install. Our pure copper marine cable can support up to 105 C (221 F) Dry and 75 C (167 F) Wet conditions

FOR MARINE BOAT SPEAKERS, BOAT CABLE - Our GearIT boat wire cable comes in 25ft, 50ft, 100ft, 125ft, 150ft, 200ft lengths and black colored trailer wire. Search on Amazon for GearIT 14 AWG Marine Speaker Cables to find all our 14 ga marine speaker wires. All GearIT marine boat speaker copper wires come with a limited lifetime warranty.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good speaker wire for the money.
reviews.reviewText: You wouldn't use this for your 20K stereo system, but for my basic boat stereo system it worked great.The cable is easy to work with. Stiff enough to push through places for routing, but not so stiff you can't work with it.I found the cable very easy to strip for connections.Sound quality was great as far as I could tell.Stereo only puts out 40W per channel, the wire seems to handle that well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great value, but not overly flexible.
reviews.reviewText: I used this wire to run power from my car's battery to a ham radio in my trunk, and an inverter under my driver seat. This wire fit the bill perfectly. It is water, oil resistant, and tinned (to resist corrosion). One challenge I ran into was its stiffness. Despite having many fine strands, the wire doesn't flex well. You can bend it, but wants to spring back and doesn't hold its shape. This made running the wire under the hood through the firewall, and along the door moulding... a LOT of work. I scraped a lot of knuckle in the process. Overall, I'd still recommend using it for automotive projects. It is a high quality wire. Just know that it's hard to manipulate though a lot of twists and turns.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality speaker wire for outdoor use
reviews.reviewText: I bought a large spool of this wire when my two story deck and patio was being built. I wanted high quality outdoor speakers and cable that was also high quality. The install went great, the deck is 95% finished and the speakers sound fantastic. The person who built my deck said that this is the cable he’s using on higher quality build outs. It may not be the cheapest, but when you are internally running wire you may not see again for 25+ years… this is the way to go

reviews.reviewText: This product is the ideal product to rewire a friend's boat lights and I even order a second roll so I could have extra wire on hand when I need it, Only con I can mention is never use Purolator as a carrier ever again. Every time an item is shipped through them it is always and I mean always late or lost in their system for days. Hence why I refuse to use them for my business requirements.
